The paper presents an algorithm for learning fault trees from observational data, which involves machine learning and artificial intelligence techniques. Therefore, cs.AI is the most likely sub-category. The paper also deals with the reliability of cyber-physical systems, which falls under the scope of cs.SE (Software Engineering) and cs.SY (Systems and Control). The paper also discusses failure modes and large amounts of data, which are relevant to cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Finally, the paper uses a population-based, randomized search method, which is a common technique in cs.LG (Machine Learning).
